Commentary Text: Cummins to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Prasidh!! The plan seems to have come off and Cummins' reaction says it all. Digs it short and lures Ishan Kishan into a hook, rushes him for pace and it's been dragged off the bottom half only to be gobbled up by PK at fine leg. The key to this dismissal was, Cummins didn't offer any width and that made things difficult for the batter. Ishan Kishan is a compulsive hooker/puller against the short ball and it seemed like a trap from KKR. Ishan Kishan c Prasidh b Cummins 1(3)

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Tripathi, out Caught by de Kock!! "Yeahhhh," shouts QdK and throws the ball high. Tripathi wears a dejected look and walks off. Rohit said it has been turning even with dew and this is turn with bounce too. Tripathi never looked comfortable. I mean he was always looking to make a statement to the bowler. This time Rahul Chahar pinned him on the crease by pitching around leg stump and this ball turned nicely, Tripathi tried to opened-up defence and nicked off. Rahul Chahar is keeping Mumbai in the game. Oh actually a pretty good grab from QdK, was a big deviation off the leading edge. Tripathi c de Kock b Rahul Chahar 5(5)
